						               													<description>From IDG - Istituto del Giuoco (Italy) and Invicta Games&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Simulation for the game of basketball. Created in cooperation with the Italian Basketball League (FIP).&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game tried to reproduce the tactics and the actions of a real basketball game.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;It is played on board of 72 rectangular cells, 36 each midfield, regulating the position of the players on the court. There are 4 distinct zones on the board:&amp;#10;1 - Inside&amp;#10;2- close shot&amp;#10;3 - long shot&amp;#10;4 - midfield&amp;#10;In each cell only 1 player of the same team can be placed and in the 'inside' area, only friendly player can be placed, simulating the 3 seconds rule.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Players have 3 attributes, Defence, Attack and Rebound. DF and AF have 4 values, from 1 to 4 growing, RF is from 1 to 10 with the higher the better.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;You can play typical defense tactics like in real basketball, and movement of player is asynchronous with the one of the ball.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game has been developed and published in 1981, so it is obviously feeling the age.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The player are simple cardboard figures on a plastic base, as well as the ball. There are no basket or any other element in 3D apart of the players themselves.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;It remarks more on the fidelity to the rules and the game more than the look.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;It can be played in 2 players, normally and a game typically lasts from 40 to 60'.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game is not language dependent for the set, but the rules are only in Italian.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
